---
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon';
import Picture from '~/components/core/Picture.astro';
---

<section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 mx-auto lg:px-8 lg:py-20 max-w-6xl">
	<div class="grid gap-6 row-gap-10 md:grid-cols-1 text-justify">
		<div class="md:pb-6 md:pr-16">
			<h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold font-heading">We guide you from idea to launch.</h2>
			<div class="flex">
				<div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-4">
					<div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full border-secondary-500 border-2">
							<Icon name="tabler:arrow-down" class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-200 icon-bold" />
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="w-px h-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-slate-500"></div>
				</div>
				<div class="pt-1 pb-8">
					<p class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-300">Step 1 : Discovery</p>
					<p>
						At the beggining, we start to mapping out a timeline and resources for the development. We connect your
						value propositions with the corresponding software requirements â€” through interviews with stakeholders and
						end-users, technical research and architecture mockups, and feedback-driven iterations.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="flex">
				<div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-4">
					<div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full border-secondary-500 border-2">
							<Icon name="tabler:arrow-down" class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-200 icon-bold" />
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="w-px h-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-slate-500"></div>
				</div>
				<div class="pt-1 pb-8">
					<p class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-300">Step 2 : Architecture & Design</p>
					<p>
						We map out the architecture and depicts the business logic of the smart contracts. <br />
						This phase is crucial and requires a lot of thought and effort to ensure the system is secure and scalable. Technical
						debt is often introduced when the wrong architecture is implemented and as time goes by it introduced will be
						compounded over time.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="flex">
				<div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-4">
					<div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full border-secondary-500 border-2">
							<Icon name="tabler:arrow-down" class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-200 icon-bold" />
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="w-px h-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-slate-500"></div>
				</div>
				<div class="pt-1 pb-8">
					<p class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-300">Step 3 : Developing smart contracts</p>
					<p>
						At cyberse, we use an agile development process to implement user-stories and features. We emphasize on
						automated testing and continuous integration to ensure the quality of the code. We also use a manual code
						review process to ensure the code is secure.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="flex">
				<div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-4">
					<div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full border-secondary-500 border-2">
							<Icon name="tabler:arrow-down" class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-200 icon-bold" />
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="w-px h-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-slate-500"></div>
				</div>
				<div class="pt-1 pb-8">
					<p class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-300">Step 4 : Security Audit</p>
					<p>
						After contracts have been implemented, we prepare a security audit from a trusted third party. First, we
						confirm that our contracts meet our security and functional requirements and that our testnet deployment
						plan is sound. Then, we examine all security warnings in our cutting-edge audit software and painstakingly
						try to find ways to improve it if needed. Finally, as an added security measure, we prepare a spreadsheet
						that organizes each test scenario and exhibits the corresponding acceptance criterion from where we would
						count the point wise coverage.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="flex">
				<div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-4">
					<div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full border-secondary-500 border-2">
							<Icon name="tabler:arrow-down" class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-200 icon-bold" />
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="w-px h-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-slate-500"></div>
				</div>
				<div class="pt-1 pb-8">
					<p class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-300">Step 5 : Deployment & Monitoring</p>
					<p>
						When the "Audit" is complete, we use our monitoring tools to visualize and analyze the behavior of our smart
						contracts and ensure that everything works fine. Between audits, however, we already established a process
						to monitor whether our contracts behave as expected with real-time alerting.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="flex">
				<div class="flex flex-col items-center mr-4">
					<div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full border-primary-600 border-2">
							<Icon name="tabler:check" class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-200 icon-bold" />
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="pt-1">
					<p class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-300">Ready!</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700"></p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="relative">
			<Picture
				class="inset-0 object-cover object-top w-full rounded-md shadow-lg md:absolute md:h-full bg-gray-400 dark:bg-slate-700"
				src={import('~/assets/images/eth_blockchain.jpg')}
				widths={[400, 768]}
				sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 432px"
				alt="Astronaut"
				aspectRatio="16:9"
			/>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
